OL,6,FBut Lord Heseltine said he had no
OL,7,Fregrets about the "battle to bring
OL,8,Funion militancy under the rule of law".
OL,10,F"I had great sympathy for the
OL,11,Fconsequences for the community, I knew
OL,12,Fwhat it would mean, but I also knew
OL,13,Fthis was a dangerous and unhealthy
OL,14,Findustry and finding alternative
OL,15,Femployment for those people engaged in
OL,16,Fit (was important).
