OL,3,CHeseltine: Victory over striking
OL,4,Cminers 'benefited communities'
OL,6,F"The beginning of the dispute in
OL,7,Fpolitical terms was 1968, when the
OL,8,FLabour government produced a white
OL,9,Fpaper indicating that there was a
OL,10,Fproblem with militant trade unions,
OL,11,Fwhich had to be dealt with by
OL,12,Fgovernment. Labour didn't do anything.
OL,14,F"I was part of the government elected
OL,15,Fin 1979. We knew we had to confront
OL,16,Fthis issue of unions outside the law
OL,17,Fof the land and of course that was the
OL,18,Fbackground to the miners strike of
OL,19,F1984.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/12
