OL,4,Cminers 'benefited communities'
OL,6,F"The police were left with the most
OL,7,Funcomfortable set of circumstances,
OL,8,Fone can argue about the odd detail in
OL,9,Fpart of the process, but you have to
OL,10,Fsee the whole situation and this was a
OL,11,Fdetermination by a group of people to
OL,12,Fimpose their views on another group of
OL,13,Fpeople, miners, who didn't want to go
OL,14,Fon strike and they were made to do so.
OL,16,F"The rule of law, the fair play that
OL,17,Fwe believe in in this country,
OL,18,Fdemanded that the public interest was
OL,19,Fprevailed and the police had to do
OL,20,Fthat."
